transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello, sir, I just signed up for the prescription today, but I would like to make a cancel.

Speaker 1: OK, give me just a second. And what's your first and last name?

Speaker 2: My first name is Adrian, and the last name is Kazako.

Speaker 1: OK, Mr. Kazako, and you don't want the order?

Speaker 2: What happened?

Speaker 1: I can cancel it for you.

Speaker 2: You don't want to get it?

Speaker 1: Because it was advertised as Viagra VGT,

Speaker 2: but they end up to be prescribed sildenafil,

Speaker 1: which I'm not OK with that.

Speaker 2: So Viagra AGV, the name is technically

Speaker 1: sildenafil, the scientific name.

Speaker 2: That's what that stands for, AGV,

Speaker 1: Authorized Generic Viagra.

Speaker 2: So any Viagra that doesn't get that blue coating

Speaker 1: on the outside is still scientifically sildenafil.

Speaker 2: So it's just a name, though.

Speaker 1: The important thing is the manufacturer

Speaker 2: that it comes from.

Speaker 1: It comes from the same facility that

Speaker 2: makes the other pills in France.

Speaker 1: It's just their newest version of the pill.

Speaker 2: So I can cancel for you, but I just wanted to let you know.

Speaker 1: That is how it works, the AGV.

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, but you should have advertised sildenafil

Speaker 1: not Viagra VGT, so yeah, I would like to cancel that.

Speaker 2: OK, no problem.

Speaker 1: All righty, so I did cancel that for you,

Speaker 2: and I refunded it for you as well.

Speaker 1: But do be careful getting other pills out there.

Speaker 2: We are the only FDA-approved company that has a license

Speaker 1: to sell this medication.

Speaker 2: So anywhere else you go, it's going

Speaker 1: to be cheap pills from India, China, definitely not

Speaker 2: legal and overseen by any sort of oversight committee.

Speaker 1: OK, so you're all set there, Mr. Adrian, OK?

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Can you send me an email with the cancellation confirmation?

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: I can do that for you.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye now.
